are served just after the soup at dinner. This is especially French;
however, this melon is more of a breakfast than a dinner dish. the water-melon
is served the same time as fruit at dinner.

Claret should be served at the same temperature as Madeira, never with ice;
it should remain about forty-eight hours standing, then decanted, care being
observed that no sediment enter the decanter.

